{"title": "Komitas the Armenian", "date_or_period": "2015", "author_or_creator": "Australian Broadcasting Corporation. Radio National", "description_or_abstract": "Komitas was a giant of Armenian music and while his musical legacy would always have been immense, the Armenian genocide of 1915 meant Komitas work was virtually the means of cultural survival of the nation. We explore the continued importance of Komitas music to Armenians today.", "url_to_original_object": "http://www.abc.net.au/radionational/image/6128646-1x1-700x700.jpg", "trove_id": "192779645", "trove_url": "https://trove.nla.gov.au/work/192779645"}
